Two views
It happens. Move onto a new project. If you're creative in more than one area, even better.
Or, get over it. Some of my favorite sci-fi/fantasy authors treated writing as a job, even if they had a "daytime" job. I won't even start on the romance authors since experienced ones can sustain a 2-3000 wpd output. There's all kind of motivational stuff on this, but start with this in your head. You are the only one that can tell this story. Without you, it dies. Pour your fucking life into it, this odd shaped bottle, be changed by it, and love it.
A good exercise is to pick up a book or movie, and figure what you'd have done differently. Then ask, why?
